# Todo Tracking System

## Todo Comment Format

When writing todos in code, use this format:

- `@todo: [description]` - Standard todo
- `@todo(priority): [description]` - Todo with priority (high/medium/low)
- `@todo(priority)[component]: [description]` - Todo with priority and component/area

Examples:

- `@todo: Refactor this function for better performance`
- `@todo(high): Fix security vulnerability in auth`
- `@todo(medium)[API]: Add rate limiting`

## Todo Tracking Commands

When asked about todos, search the codebase for @todo comments and:

1. List all todos found
2. Group by priority if specified (high → medium → low → unspecified)
3. Group by component/area if specified
4. Show file path and line context for each
5. Provide a count summary

## Proactive Todo Suggestions

When reviewing or writing code, suggest adding @todo comments for:

- Obvious performance improvements
- Missing error handling
- Incomplete implementations
- Technical debt
- Missing tests or documentation
